 :tx/rationale "Create task: SOUND-LIVE: LIVE view retraction guard — detect bare retractions that leave ghost values. CONTEXT: Both from_datoms() (store.rs:1052) and apply_datoms() (store.rs:1124) guard LIVE view updates with 'if d.op == Op::Assert'. Retract datoms are inserted into BTreeSet and all secondary indexes but NEVER update live_view. A bare retraction (without paired assert) leaves the retracted value visible in live_view forever. All code that reads current state via live_view — status, guidance, routing, seed — sees ghost values. The protocol uses retract-then-assert (ADR-COHERENCE-001) but this invariant is NOWHERE ENFORCED. RATIONALE: This is the highest-risk silent-corruption path in the store. Every query via live_view could return stale data if the retract-then-assert protocol is violated anywhere. A debug_assert costs zero in release builds and converts silent corruption to loud failure. APPROACH: (1) In apply_datoms(), after processing all datoms in a batch, scan for bare retractions: any (entity, attribute) pair that has a Retract datom in this batch but no corresponding Assert datom in this batch AND the live_view entry was not updated (i.e., the live_view still points to the retracted value). (2) Emit debug_assert\\!(false, 'bare retraction on ({:?}, {:?}) without paired assert — live_view may contain ghost value', entity, attribute). (3) Add a unit test test_live_view_retract_then_assert that verifies the protocol works: assert V1, retract V1, assert V2 in same tx — live_view should show V2. (4) Add a unit test test_live_view_bare_retract that verifies the debug_assert fires: assert V1 in tx1, retract V1 in tx2 without re-assert — live_view still shows V1 (documenting the known limitation). ACCEPTANCE: (A) debug_assert added to apply_datoms. (B) test_live_view_retract_then_assert passes — live_view correctly shows V2 after retract-then-assert. (C) test_live_view_bare_retract documents the limitation — live_view shows V1 after bare retract (with a comment explaining this is the known gap). (D) No performance regression in release builds (debug_assert is compiled out). (E) All existing tests pass. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs (apply_datoms, from_datoms, test module). TRACES-TO: INV-STORE-012 (LIVE view correctness), ADR-COHERENCE-001 (retract-then-assert)."
